The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Steel melts at home

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, June 26: Steel stocks sank in India as the sensex swooned on a day of relentless bear hammering, but elsewhere in Asia they perked up sharply on the expectation that the creation of an Arcelor-Mittal combine would bring in some pricing discipline and consolidation in a notoriously commoditised industry.

 Broking circles said the stock markets here had already discounted the Arcelor-Mittal deal. 

 While steel shares saw sharp rises last week on account of the benefits that could flow to the industry globally from the deal, this was not the case today as realisation dawned that there would not be any significant gains for domestic steel manufacturers. 




